void
Globals
[in] IL2_state [in, out] IL2_Functions_S [in,out] IL2_PIM_PSO_Parameters
Input->Output-Correlation
All described correlations occur only if:
BAPHandler_IL2 is in state stateIL2_run (standard run state)
BAP message has proper indication type (BapInd_DataSetGet)
pointer to existing array with non zero length was provided If such case, the Brightnes value is verified. If it is in expected range, new value is stored in structure IL2_Functions_S, default flag is reset and isDirty flag is set to PSO_DIRTYSTATE_DIRTY. If new Brightness value differs form the previous value it is stored in IL2_PIM_PSO_Parameters (the mirror of NvM) and new value is provided to InteriorLight2. Otherwise, when Brightnes value not met the range condition, out of range message is send as response.
